------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This is essentially a placeholder for the next release note ...
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  o New features
    * none

  o New optimization
    * Burst buffer driver data log buffering layer removed. Buffering layer 
      was intended to align data log write to 8MiB striping boundary on 
      Cray DataWarp. However, experiment shows negligible performance 
      improvement unless the I/O request is extremely small and fragment. 
      Instead, it reduce performance on usual and larger request size. The 
      buffering layer is removed. Data log now writes directly to the BB using 
      POSIX API.

